President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Arkansas due to a severe winter storm that occurred in January 2009. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The affected counties include Baxter, Benton, Boone, Carroll, Clay, Craighead, Franklin, Fulton, Greene, Independence, Izard, Jackson, Johnson, Lawrence, Madison, Marion, Mississippi, Newton, Searcy, Sharp, Stone, Van Buren, and Washington. W. Michael Moore has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Damage assessments are still ongoing, and more counties may be eligible for assistance based on the final assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-4600.